00:47:27,637 --> 00:47:30,807
You haven't told
bedtime stories before.

517
00:47:30,890 --> 00:47:33,101
Uh, not too many, no.

518
00:47:33,184 --> 00:47:35,687
Well, you have to add
some twists and stuff.

519
00:47:37,105 --> 00:47:39,440
OK. Some twists.

520
00:47:41,234 --> 00:47:44,404
Like what kind of twists?
Give me an example.

521
00:47:45,697 --> 00:47:47,782
Maybe they run out of gas.

522
00:47:47,866 --> 00:47:49,868
They run out of gas?

523
00:47:49,951 --> 00:47:53,037
That's good
'cause they're driving, right? OK...

524
00:47:53,121 --> 00:47:55,498
Tell me the story
about why you're sad.

525
00:47:58,167 --> 00:48:00,336
You think I'm sad?

526
00:48:03,089 --> 00:48:05,258
What makes you think that?

527
00:48:07,135 --> 00:48:09,304
Your eyes told me.

528
00:48:11,055 --> 00:48:13,892
I'm not supposed to talk
about stuff like that.

529
00:48:19,898 --> 00:48:21,900
[exhales]

530
00:48:24,986 --> 00:48:28,406
Once upon a time, there was
this person named Malcolm.

531
00:48:28,489 --> 00:48:32,160
He worked with children.

532
00:48:32,243 --> 00:48:34,829
He loved it.

533
00:48:34,913 --> 00:48:37,582
He loved it more than anything else.

534
00:48:40,335 --> 00:48:43,671
And then one night,
he found out that he made a...

535
00:48:43,713 --> 00:48:45,882
...mistake with one of them.

536
00:48:45,965 --> 00:48:48,301
He couldn't help that one.

537
00:48:49,844 --> 00:48:54,515
And he can't stop thinking
about it. He... can't forget.

538
00:48:57,977 --> 00:49:00,647
Ever since then,
things have been different.

539
00:49:02,065 --> 00:49:05,109
He's not the same person
that he used to be.

540
00:49:07,111 --> 00:49:11,866
And his wife... doesn't like
the person that he's become.

541
00:49:11,908 --> 00:49:15,912
They barely speak anymore.
They're like strangers.

542
00:49:19,040 --> 00:49:22,669
And then one day, Malcolm
meets this wonderful little boy.

543
00:49:22,710 --> 00:49:25,546
A really cool little boy.

544
00:49:26,881 --> 00:49:29,384
Reminds him a lot of the other one.

545
00:49:31,719 --> 00:49:34,973
And Malcolm decides
to try and help this new boy...

546
00:49:37,058 --> 00:49:41,771
...'cause he feels that
if he can help this new boy,

547
00:49:41,854 --> 00:49:46,192
be like... helping that other one too.

548
00:49:49,153 --> 00:49:51,906
How does the story end?

549
00:49:53,449 --> 00:49:55,451
I don't know.

550
00:50:12,844 --> 00:50:16,014
I want to tell you my secret now.

551
00:50:20,101 --> 00:50:21,769
OK.

552
00:50:29,485 --> 00:50:32,321
I see dead people.

553
00:50:34,907 --> 00:50:36,909
In your dreams?

554
00:50:39,037 --> 00:50:41,122
While you're awake?

555
00:50:46,836 --> 00:50:50,506
Dead people, like,
in graves and coffins?

556
00:50:50,590 --> 00:50:53,801
Walking around like regular people.

557
00:50:53,885 --> 00:50:56,888
They don't see each other.

558
00:50:56,971 --> 00:51:00,308
They only see what they want to see.

559
00:51:01,267 --> 00:51:03,603
They don't know they're dead.

560
00:51:05,730 --> 00:51:08,399
How often do you see them?

561
00:51:11,486 --> 00:51:14,322
All the time.

562
00:51:16,365 --> 00:51:18,868
They're everywhere.

563
00:51:21,329 --> 00:51:24,457
You won't tell anyone my secret, right?

564
00:51:24,499 --> 00:51:27,251
No. I promise.

565
00:51:29,087 --> 00:51:32,215
Will you stay here until I fall asleep?

566
00:51:34,008 --> 00:51:35,843
Of course.

567
00:51:44,477 --> 00:51:46,521
[Click]

568
00:51:46,604 --> 00:51:51,400
[Malcolm] Cole... has pathologies
more severe than initially assessed.

569
00:51:53,277 --> 00:51:56,155
He's suffering
from visual hallucinations,

570
00:51:56,197 --> 00:51:58,908
- paranoia...
- [tyres screeching]

571
00:51:58,991 --> 00:52:03,329
...some kind of...
school-age schizophrenia.

572
00:52:05,164 --> 00:52:08,835
Medication, hospitalisation
may be required.

573
00:52:14,132 --> 00:52:16,968
[sighs] And I'm not helping him.

574
00:53:25,786 --> 00:53:27,663
[sighs]

575
00:53:39,133 --> 00:53:41,135
[clears throat]

576
00:53:44,639 --> 00:53:47,141
Hi. This is Lynn Sear, Cole's mom.

577
00:53:48,768 --> 00:53:52,980
Yeah. Uh, yeah, I-I'd like
to talk to you about your boy

578
00:53:53,022 --> 00:53:56,359
and his friends keeping
their goddamn hands off my son.

579
00:55:18,899 --> 00:55:21,235
[shuffling]

580
00:55:33,998 --> 00:55:35,833
Mama?

581
00:55:36,667 --> 00:55:38,169
No.

582
00:55:38,252 --> 00:55:40,338
Dinner is not ready!

583
00:55:40,421 --> 00:55:42,089
What are you gonna do?

584
00:55:42,131 --> 00:55:44,508
Y-You can't hurt me anymore!

585
00:55:46,719 --> 00:55:49,722
Lenny, you're
a terrible husband, Lenny!

586
00:55:49,764 --> 00:55:53,059
Look what you made me do! Lenny!

587
00:55:53,100 --> 00:55:55,436
[Cole sobbing]

588
00:56:03,486 --> 00:56:06,947
[panting] I'm OK. OK. OK.

589
00:56:12,328 --> 00:56:14,580
[Tommy] Once there was a boy,

590
00:56:14,622 --> 00:56:17,416
very different from all the other boys.

591
00:56:17,458 --> 00:56:20,127
He lived in the jungle...

592
00:56:21,295 --> 00:56:24,090
...and he could speak
to the animals.

593
00:56:24,131 --> 00:56:27,468
- [piano music]
- [camcorders whirring]

594
00:56:28,511 --> 00:56:31,639
[kids making animal noises]

595
00:56:31,680 --> 00:56:33,849
[applause]

596
00:56:38,938 --> 00:56:41,690
[Cole] Did you think
the play sucked big time?

597
00:56:41,774 --> 00:56:44,652
Heh. What?

598
00:56:44,735 --> 00:56:47,738
Tommy Tammisimo acted
in a cough syrup commercial.

599
00:56:47,822 --> 00:56:51,075
He said everyone was
self-conscious and unrealistic.

600
00:56:51,158 --> 00:56:53,411
He said the play sucked big time.

601
00:56:53,494 --> 00:56:56,247
This Tommy kid sounds like a real punk.

602
00:56:57,915 --> 00:57:01,919
I thought the play was
excellent. Better than Cats.

603
00:57:02,002 --> 00:57:04,505
- Cats?
- Never mind.

604
00:57:06,340 --> 00:57:08,259
Cole, I was really interested

605
00:57:08,342 --> 00:57:10,469
in what you told me at the hospital.

606
00:57:10,511 --> 00:57:13,013
I'd like to hear more about it.

607
00:57:23,107 --> 00:57:24,942
Cole?

608
00:57:27,862 --> 00:57:29,530
What?

609
00:57:42,710 --> 00:57:44,712
Something up there?

610
00:57:49,508 --> 00:57:51,343
Cole?

611
00:57:54,889 --> 00:57:56,891
I don't see anything.

612
00:58:01,270 --> 00:58:03,272
Be real still.

613
00:58:07,902 --> 00:58:10,237
Sometimes you feel it inside,

614
00:58:10,321 --> 00:58:13,032
like you're falling down real fast,

615
00:58:13,073 --> 00:58:15,743
but you're really just standing still.

616
00:58:20,664 --> 00:58:25,085
Do you ever feel the prickly
things on the back of your neck?

617
00:58:25,127 --> 00:58:27,796
Yes.

618
00:58:27,880 --> 00:58:31,967
And the tiny hairs on your arm,
you know, when they stand up?

619
00:58:32,051 --> 00:58:33,886
Yes.

620
00:58:36,222 --> 00:58:38,224
That's them.

621
00:58:41,519 --> 00:58:43,687
When they get mad...

622
00:58:47,775 --> 00:58:49,777
...it gets cold.

623
00:59:06,919 --> 00:59:10,923
I don't see anything.
Are you sure they're there?

624
00:59:12,591 --> 00:59:14,426
Cole?

625
00:59:16,554 --> 00:59:19,431
Please make them leave.

626
00:59:19,473 --> 00:59:21,475
I'm workin' on it.

627
00:59:23,852 --> 00:59:25,688
Come on.

628
00:59:53,215 --> 00:59:56,218
Aah! [laughing]

629
01:00:11,025 --> 01:00:13,360
<i>Mommy, Daddy?</i>

630
01:00:14,486 --> 01:00:16,363
[coughing]

631
01:00:16,405 --> 01:00:18,741
<i>My throat hurts.</i>

632
01:00:27,291 --> 01:00:29,126
<i>Run! Run!</i>

633
01:00:30,711 --> 01:00:33,005
[announcer]
<i>Pedia Ease cough suppressant.</i>

634
01:00:33,047 --> 01:00:35,424
<i>Gentle, fast, eff...</i>

635
01:00:35,507 --> 01:00:37,760
Cole.

636
01:00:37,843 --> 01:00:41,555
Oh, I don't care what they say.
This thing is broken.

637
01:00:49,396 --> 01:00:51,398
Take 'em off.

638
01:00:55,319 --> 01:00:57,488
I don't want them on my table.

639
01:01:02,201 --> 01:01:05,371
I saw what was in your bureau
drawer when I was cleaning.

640
01:01:05,412 --> 01:01:07,623
Got something you want to confess?

641
01:01:10,584 --> 01:01:12,169
Hmm?

642
01:01:12,252 --> 01:01:15,923
The bumblebee pendant?
Why do you keep taking it?

643
01:01:20,552 --> 01:01:22,721
It was Grandma's.

644
01:01:22,763 --> 01:01:26,100
You know, what if it broke?
You know how sad I'd be.

645
01:01:28,268 --> 01:01:31,271
You'd cry 'cause you
miss Grandma so much.

646
01:01:32,272 --> 01:01:34,274
That's right.

647
01:01:38,529 --> 01:01:42,199
Sometimes people think
they lose things...

648
01:01:43,992 --> 01:01:47,830
...and they really didn't
lose them, it just gets moved.

649
01:01:47,913 --> 01:01:50,416
So did you move
the bumblebee pendant?

650
01:01:58,298 --> 01:02:00,217
Don't get mad.

651
01:02:00,300 --> 01:02:02,344
So who moved it this time?

652
01:02:02,428 --> 01:02:05,764
Maybe someone came in our house,
took the bumblebee pendant

653
01:02:05,806 --> 01:02:08,892
out of my closet and placed
it nicely in your drawer.

654
01:02:10,144 --> 01:02:13,564
- Maybe.
- God, I am so tired, Cole.

655
01:02:13,647 --> 01:02:16,150
I'm tired in my body,
I'm tired in my mind,

656
01:02:16,191 --> 01:02:18,986
I'm... tired in my heart.

657
01:02:19,069 --> 01:02:22,322
I need some help. You know,
I don't know if you noticed,

658
01:02:22,406 --> 01:02:25,701
but our little family
isn't doing so good.

659
01:02:25,784 --> 01:02:30,164
I mean, I've been praying,
but I must not be praying right.

660
01:02:30,205 --> 01:02:34,668
Looks like we're just gonna have
to answer each other's prayers.

661
01:02:37,546 --> 01:02:40,716
If we can't talk to each other,
we're not gonna make it.

662
01:02:44,052 --> 01:02:47,723
Now, tell me, baby.
I-l... I won't get mad, honey.

663
01:02:47,806 --> 01:02:50,642
Did you take the bumblebee pendant?

664
01:02:58,859 --> 01:03:01,361
- No.
- [silverware clatters]

665
01:03:03,071 --> 01:03:06,408
You've had enough roast beef.
You need to leave the table.

666
01:03:08,452 --> 01:03:10,120
Go!

667
01:03:20,672 --> 01:03:23,175
[barking, whimpering]

668
01:03:27,387 --> 01:03:29,223
[gasps]

669
01:03:33,310 --> 01:03:35,229
Hey, come on.

670
01:03:35,312 --> 01:03:38,148
I'll show you where
my dad keeps his gun. Come on.

671
01:03:40,818 --> 01:03:42,653
[dog whimpering]

672
01:03:43,946 --> 01:03:47,366
[sobbing] Sebastian, come on.

673
01:03:47,407 --> 01:03:49,243
Mama?

674
01:03:55,916 --> 01:03:58,585
If you're not very mad,

675
01:03:58,669 --> 01:04:01,338
can I sleep in your bed tonight?

676
01:04:03,173 --> 01:04:05,676
Look at my face.

677
01:04:05,759 --> 01:04:07,928
I'm not very mad.

678
01:04:13,058 --> 01:04:15,561
Baby, why are you shaking?

679
01:04:16,645 --> 01:04:18,814
Cole, what's wrong?

680
01:04:18,897 --> 01:04:22,693
Oh, God, please tell me!

681
01:04:22,776 --> 01:04:24,778
Oh, please.

682
01:04:28,323 --> 01:04:30,158
Oh.

683
01:04:38,959 --> 01:04:40,961
[Anna] It's Edwardian,

684
01:04:41,003 --> 01:04:43,797
beautifully worked
with mine-cut diamonds

685
01:04:43,881 --> 01:04:47,134
and an actual colour Burmese sapphire.

686
01:04:47,217 --> 01:04:49,845
It's timeless.

687
01:04:49,928 --> 01:04:51,763
Oh.

688
01:04:52,723 --> 01:04:54,975
You, uh... [clears throat]

689
01:04:55,058 --> 01:04:57,227
...got anything a little plainer?

690
01:04:57,311 --> 01:04:59,146
Plainer?

691
01:04:59,187 --> 01:05:02,816
You want a plain ring to go with
your plain fiancé? Is that how it is?

692
01:05:02,900 --> 01:05:06,069
No! Baby, don't... don't get in a tizzy.

693
01:05:08,906 --> 01:05:10,657
Uh...

694
01:05:10,741 --> 01:05:13,452
You're so beautiful.

695
01:05:13,493 --> 01:05:17,164
Y-You're like a Burmese
sapphire all by yourself.

696
01:05:17,247 --> 01:05:20,208
- You don't need all that.
- Uh-huh.

697
01:05:20,292 --> 01:05:24,963
Why don't you try it on and see
how you both feel about it?

698
01:05:30,344 --> 01:05:32,679
There. How does that feel?

699
01:05:34,014 --> 01:05:37,643
I think this piece, um,
communicates a longing.

700
01:05:37,684 --> 01:05:41,313
I imagine that the woman who owned it

701
01:05:41,355 --> 01:05:44,191
loved a man that she couldn't be with.

702
01:05:45,943 --> 01:05:49,154
Did he have wavy hair and chestnut eyes?

703
01:05:49,196 --> 01:05:53,325
- What?
- Um, I-l don't know, but...

704
01:05:53,367 --> 01:05:56,328
...a lot of the pieces
in this store communicate,

705
01:05:56,370 --> 01:05:59,706
and I think you should choose
a piece that speaks to you.

706
01:06:01,333 --> 01:06:05,420
I think maybe when people own
things and then they pass away,

707
01:06:05,504 --> 01:06:09,633
a part of themselves gets
printed on those things,

708
01:06:09,716 --> 01:06:13,220
like... like fingerprints.

709
01:06:14,763 --> 01:06:16,932
I'll just wrap it up.

710
01:06:24,356 --> 01:06:26,608
You don't need a guy with a master's.

711
01:06:26,692 --> 01:06:29,778
You need a wrestler with
a neck larger than his head.

712
01:06:29,861 --> 01:06:32,781
[chuckles] No, I need
a wrestler with a master's.

713
01:06:34,116 --> 01:06:36,576
- What's this?
- Happy birthday.

714
01:06:36,618 --> 01:06:38,620
- From you?
- Mm-hmm.

715
01:06:46,420 --> 01:06:48,422
It's a...

716
01:06:48,505 --> 01:06:50,590
...first edition.

717
01:06:50,674 --> 01:06:52,592
- Wow.
- [giggles]

718
01:06:52,676 --> 01:06:54,845
Oh, this is too much.

719
01:06:54,928 --> 01:06:58,432
No. Took it out
of your Christmas bonus.

720
01:06:59,850 --> 01:07:02,602
It's perfect, Anna.

721
01:07:02,686 --> 01:07:04,771
Thanks.

722
01:07:04,855 --> 01:07:06,857
[chuckles]

723
01:07:10,610 --> 01:07:13,572
<i>[Cole] What do you want
more than anything?</i>

724
01:07:13,613 --> 01:07:15,615
<i>[Malcolm] I don't know.</i>

725
01:07:15,699 --> 01:07:17,826
<i>[Cole] I told you what I want.</i>

726
01:07:17,909 --> 01:07:20,245
. [bang], glass breaking]
<i>'</i> [gasps]

727
01:07:21,455 --> 01:07:23,623
<i>[Malcolm] I know what I want.</i>

728
01:07:25,500 --> 01:07:28,336
<i>I want to be able
to talk to my wife again...</i>

729
01:07:30,130 --> 01:07:32,632
<i>...the way we used
to talk to each other...</i>

730
01:07:34,176 --> 01:07:36,928
<i>...like there was no one
else in the world except us.</i>

731
01:07:38,805 --> 01:07:40,974
<i>[Cole] How are you gonna do that?</i>

732
01:07:44,144 --> 01:07:46,104
[sighs]

733
01:07:46,146 --> 01:07:48,482
I can't be
your doctor anymore.

734
01:07:48,523 --> 01:07:52,569
I haven't paid enough
attention to my family.

735
01:07:52,652 --> 01:07:55,322
Bad things happen
when you do that.

736
01:07:56,823 --> 01:07:59,451
Do you understand?

737
01:07:59,493 --> 01:08:02,079
I'm going to transfer you.
I know two psychol...

738
01:08:02,162 --> 01:08:04,498
Don't fail me.

739
01:08:05,999 --> 01:08:09,920
Don't give up. You're the only
one who can help me. I know it.

740
01:08:10,003 --> 01:08:12,172
I can't help you.

741
01:08:14,841 --> 01:08:17,177
You...

742
01:08:17,260 --> 01:08:19,596
Someone else can help you.

743
01:08:22,516 --> 01:08:24,851
You believe me, right?

744
01:08:29,356 --> 01:08:32,192
Dr Crowe, you believe my secret, right?

745
01:08:34,069 --> 01:08:37,114
I don't know how
to answer that, Cole.

746
01:08:47,124 --> 01:08:50,043
How can you help me...

747
01:08:50,085 --> 01:08:52,754
...if you don't believe me?

748
01:08:56,716 --> 01:08:59,719
Some magic's real.

749
01:09:15,861 --> 01:09:19,197
[Vincent] Do you know why
you're afraid when you're alone?

750
01:09:21,199 --> 01:09:24,161
I do. I do.

751
01:09:28,081 --> 01:09:29,791
[click, tape hissing]

752
01:09:29,875 --> 01:09:32,252
<i>[Malcolm] I'm sorry about that, Vincent.</i>

753
01:09:32,335 --> 01:09:35,046
<i>I hope I didn't leave
you alone too long.</i>

754
01:09:35,088 --> 01:09:38,758
- <i>Whew. It's</i> cold in here.
- [Vincent sobbing]

755
01:09:41,094 --> 01:09:44,264
<i>Vincent, why are you crying?</i>

756
01:09:48,768 --> 01:09:52,606
[Vincent sniffles]
You won't believe.

757
01:09:56,568 --> 01:09:58,653
<i>- [click]
- I'm sorry about that, Vincent.</i>

758
01:09:58,737 --> 01:10:01,656
<i>I hope I didn't leave
you alone too long.</i>

759
01:10:01,740 --> 01:10:05,243
<i>- Whew. It's cold in here.
- [sobbing]</i>

760
01:10:06,703 --> 01:10:09,915
- Vincent...
- [click, whirring]

761
01:10:09,956 --> 01:10:12,959
- [click]
- <i>Whew. It's</i> cold in here.

762
01:10:13,043 --> 01:10:15,128
[sobbing]

763
01:10:20,425 --> 01:10:22,552
- [click]
- [Malcolm] No, you know <i>what?</i>

764
01:10:22,636 --> 01:10:23,929
<i>I never liked 'em either.</i>

765
01:10:23,970 --> 01:10:26,473
<i>When I was a kid,
I had this blood test done,</i>

766
01:10:26,514 --> 01:10:30,185
<i>and I threw up chilli cheese
fries all over this male nurse.</i>

767
01:10:30,268 --> 01:10:32,479
- [Vincent giggles]
- [knocking, door opens]

768
01:10:32,562 --> 01:10:34,981
<i>[woman] Excuse me.
Dr Reed is on line two.</i>

769
01:10:35,065 --> 01:10:37,817
<i>Vincent, will you excuse me?
I have to take this.</i>

770
01:10:37,901 --> 01:10:40,403
<i>- Just give me a minute, OK?
- OK.</i>

771
01:10:43,031 --> 01:10:44,866
[door shuts]

772
01:10:51,122 --> 01:10:52,958
[soft whine]

773
01:10:59,631 --> 01:11:01,633
[Vincent panting]

774
01:11:23,029 --> 01:11:26,324
[faint voice, indistinct]

775
01:11:38,962 --> 01:11:41,047
[tape hissing loudly]

776
01:11:41,089 --> 01:11:42,924
[Vincent breathing heavily]

777
01:11:43,008 --> 01:11:45,677
[faint voice continues]

778
01:11:50,598 --> 01:11:53,810
[man speaking Spanish]

779
01:11:53,893 --> 01:11:55,729
<i>No entiendes.</i>

780
01:11:55,812 --> 01:11:57,689
<i>No entiendes.</i>

781
01:11:57,731 --> 01:12:00,567
<i>Yo no quiero morir.</i>

782
01:12:00,608 --> 01:12:03,778
Yo no quiero morir...
[continues in Spanish]

783
01:12:07,782 --> 01:12:09,409
<i>Yo no quiero morir.</i>

784
01:12:09,451 --> 01:12:12,746
<i>- Oh, my God.
- Yo no quiero morir!</i>

785
01:12:18,752 --> 01:12:21,087
You been running around?

786
01:12:24,507 --> 01:12:27,010
Make you feel better?

787
01:12:28,261 --> 01:12:31,014
I like to run around.
It's good exercise.

788
01:12:34,517 --> 01:12:36,895
Do you wanna ask me questions now?

789
01:12:38,980 --> 01:12:42,650
Wanna be a lance corporal in Company M,
Third Battalion, Seventh Marines?

790
01:12:42,734 --> 01:12:45,612
We're being dispatched
into the Quang Nam province.

791
01:12:45,653 --> 01:12:47,489
Maybe later.

792
01:12:50,283 --> 01:12:52,577
Something happened, didn't it?

793
01:12:54,662 --> 01:12:57,040
You wiggin' out?

794
01:12:59,292 --> 01:13:01,044
Yes.

795
01:13:01,127 --> 01:13:02,962
I think I am.

796
01:13:05,340 --> 01:13:08,968
[Malcolm] Do you know what
"yo no <i>quiero</i> morir" means?

797
01:13:09,010 --> 01:13:12,430
It's Spanish. It means
"I don't want to die".

798
01:13:14,766 --> 01:13:17,936
What do you think these ghosts
want when they talk to you?

799
01:13:25,527 --> 01:13:27,695
I want you to think about it, Cole.

800
01:13:29,280 --> 01:13:32,617
I want you to think
about it really carefully.

801
01:13:32,659 --> 01:13:34,828
What do you think they want?

802
01:13:38,832 --> 01:13:40,667
Just help.

803
01:13:40,708 --> 01:13:43,545
That's right. That's what I think too.

804
01:13:43,628 --> 01:13:46,381
They just want help,
even the scary ones.

805
01:13:46,464 --> 01:13:49,509
And I think I might know
a way to make them go away.

806
01:13:49,551 --> 01:13:51,344
How?

807
01:13:52,303 --> 01:13:54,305
Listen to them.

808
01:13:56,266 --> 01:13:58,435
What if they don't want help?

809
01:13:58,518 --> 01:14:02,021
What if they're just angry and
they just want to hurt somebody?

810
01:14:02,063 --> 01:14:04,399
I don't think that's the way it works.

811
01:14:04,482 --> 01:14:06,484
How do you know for sure?

812
01:14:08,611 --> 01:14:10,447
I don't.

813
01:14:31,259 --> 01:14:32,927
Hey.

814
01:14:34,053 --> 01:14:36,222
Hey! Hey!

815
01:14:53,281 --> 01:14:55,867
[Lynn sobbing]

816
01:14:55,909 --> 01:14:57,911
What's happening?

817
01:14:59,245 --> 01:15:01,581
What's... what's happening?

818
01:15:03,166 --> 01:15:05,001
Cole!

819
01:15:08,588 --> 01:15:10,423
What's...

820
01:15:13,426 --> 01:15:15,428
[panting]

821
01:15:18,139 --> 01:15:20,850
What's happening to you?

822
01:15:20,934 --> 01:15:24,145
Is someone hurting you?
I'll... I will kick their ass.

823
01:15:24,229 --> 01:15:26,397
Cole, if they're hurting you...

824
01:15:28,274 --> 01:15:30,944
[groaning]

825
01:15:33,404 --> 01:15:35,240
[sighs]

826
01:15:39,911 --> 01:15:42,080
Mama, you sleep now.

827
01:15:57,011 --> 01:15:59,013
[panting]

828
01:16:22,537 --> 01:16:24,539
[snapping]

829
01:16:35,842 --> 01:16:37,343
Aah!

830
01:16:41,764 --> 01:16:44,225
[sobbing, panting]

831
01:17:38,946 --> 01:17:41,324
[retching]

832
01:17:43,451 --> 01:17:45,244
[Spits]

833
01:17:45,328 --> 01:17:47,413
[sobbing]

834
01:17:49,707 --> 01:17:52,293
I'm feeling much better now.

835
01:17:56,631 --> 01:17:59,634
D-Do you want to tell me something?

836
01:18:05,765 --> 01:18:07,934
[engine running]

837
01:18:18,736 --> 01:18:21,072
[brakes squeaking]

838
01:18:28,454 --> 01:18:29,664
[gasps]

839
01:18:35,753 --> 01:18:38,756
She came a long way
to visit me, didn't she?

840
01:18:40,133 --> 01:18:42,135
I guess she did.

841
01:19:02,739 --> 01:19:05,241
[woman sobbing]

842
01:19:19,005 --> 01:19:21,340
[woman sobbing]

843
01:19:28,765 --> 01:19:30,767
Can you get some water?

844
01:19:34,729 --> 01:19:36,731
That's her sister.

845
01:19:39,859 --> 01:19:41,861
[sobbing]

846
01:19:54,540 --> 01:19:58,878
[woman 1] ...you know, and I went
through this with my father's cancer...

847
01:19:58,920 --> 01:20:02,340
I just can't imagine a child
being in bed for two years.

848
01:20:02,381 --> 01:20:04,926
[woman 2] How many...
how many doctors?

849
01:20:05,009 --> 01:20:07,887
- I think it was six.
- Six different doctors?

850
01:20:07,929 --> 01:20:10,640
- I think so, yes.
- Oh.

851
01:20:16,103 --> 01:20:20,608
I just heard the, uh...
the little one is falling ill now.

852
01:20:20,691 --> 01:20:22,693
God help them.

853
01:20:42,630 --> 01:20:45,174
Don't go home, OK?

854
01:20:45,258 --> 01:20:47,260
I definitely won't.

855
01:21:42,982 --> 01:21:44,108
Aah!

856
01:21:44,150 --> 01:21:45,985
[panting]

857
01:22:46,128 --> 01:22:47,964
Mister?

858
01:22:51,550 --> 01:22:53,552
Excuse me, mister.

859
01:22:58,140 --> 01:23:00,643
Are you Kyra's daddy?

860
01:23:14,198 --> 01:23:16,200
It's for you.

861
01:23:17,868 --> 01:23:20,705
Sh-She wanted to tell you something.

862
01:23:58,492 --> 01:24:01,787
<i>[Kyra] Oh, no! Here he comes!
Look, he's coming my way. Psst.</i>

863
01:24:05,916 --> 01:24:07,918
<i>Would you like to dance?</i>

864
01:24:09,378 --> 01:24:12,923
<i>Um, well, actually,
I just came with my friends.</i>

865
01:24:12,965 --> 01:24:15,593
<i>Oh. Well, how about this?</i>

866
01:24:15,634 --> 01:24:17,595
<i>We can dance for a little bit,</i>

867
01:24:17,636 --> 01:24:19,597
<i>and if you don't like the way I dance,</i>

868
01:24:19,638 --> 01:24:21,474
<i>y-you can kick me.</i>

869
01:24:21,557 --> 01:24:23,559
<i>Oh. OK then.</i>

870
01:25:19,865 --> 01:25:21,700
[Splash]

871
01:25:32,711 --> 01:25:35,381
<i>It's time for lunch, Kyra.</i>

872
01:25:40,719 --> 01:25:44,098
<i>- I'm feeling much better now.
- That's so great, honey.</i>

873
01:25:44,181 --> 01:25:46,183
<i>It's time for your food.</i>

874
01:25:47,810 --> 01:25:49,728
<i>Can I go outside if I eat this?</i>

875
01:25:49,812 --> 01:25:52,857
<i>I don't know. You know how
you get sick in the afternoons.</i>

876
01:25:52,898 --> 01:25:54,733
We'll see.

877
01:25:56,569 --> 01:25:58,529
<i>Don't say that it tastes funny.</i>

878
01:25:58,571 --> 01:26:01,240
<i>You know I don't like to hear that.</i>

879
01:26:03,409 --> 01:26:05,411
<i>Sammie's mom called.</i>

880
01:26:23,262 --> 01:26:25,431
You were keeping her sick.

881
01:26:42,823 --> 01:26:45,326
You liked it, she said.

882
01:26:48,162 --> 01:26:50,331
She looked out for you.

883
01:26:51,540 --> 01:26:54,084
Is Kyra coming back?

884
01:26:56,921 --> 01:26:58,923
Not anymore.

885
01:27:05,971 --> 01:27:08,390
- [Cole] All right.
- [woman] I think that's enough.

886
01:27:08,474 --> 01:27:10,476
- That's enough makeup.
- OK.

887
01:27:11,810 --> 01:27:13,979
They're calling for the stable boy.

888
01:27:14,063 --> 01:27:16,065
Oh, we have to hurry!

889
01:27:18,150 --> 01:27:21,695
Who, uh... who were you talking to?

890
01:27:28,244 --> 01:27:30,412
Just practising my lines.

891
01:27:34,124 --> 01:27:37,044
[Cole] Thanks for giving me
this part, Mr Cunningham.

892
01:27:37,127 --> 01:27:41,048
When I went to school here, there
was a terrible fire in the theatre.

893
01:27:41,131 --> 01:27:43,133
They rebuilt the whole thing.

894
01:27:43,175 --> 01:27:45,010
Yeah, I know.

895
01:27:46,512 --> 01:27:49,014
[audience] Aw.

896
01:27:56,188 --> 01:27:58,482
Only he who is pure of heart

897
01:27:58,524 --> 01:28:01,318
can take the sword from the stone.

898
01:28:01,360 --> 01:28:03,362
Let the boy try.

899
01:28:05,864 --> 01:28:08,033
[scattered applause]

900
01:28:10,953 --> 01:28:14,039
But he is a stable boy.
He cleans up after the horses.

901
01:28:14,123 --> 01:28:16,125
Silence, village idiot.

902
01:28:17,376 --> 01:28:20,045
Let the boy step forward.

903
01:28:44,153 --> 01:28:46,155
[all gasp]

904
01:28:47,156 --> 01:28:50,075
[all] Hail King Arthur!

905
01:28:50,159 --> 01:28:52,161
[applause]

906
01:28:55,539 --> 01:28:57,791
[kids] Yea!

907
01:28:57,875 --> 01:29:00,127
- Hoorah!
- [applause]

908
01:29:00,210 --> 01:29:02,379
[kids shouting]

909
01:29:06,175 --> 01:29:08,344
[audience laughing]

910
01:29:09,470 --> 01:29:11,972
[applause resumes]

911
01:29:17,686 --> 01:29:19,855
[kids chattering]

912
01:29:22,524 --> 01:29:25,194
I thought you were really
great in the play, Cole.

913
01:29:25,277 --> 01:29:27,696
- Really?
- Yeah.

914
01:29:27,780 --> 01:29:30,324
- You know what else?
- What?

915
01:29:30,407 --> 01:29:33,327
I thought Tommy Tammisimo
sucked big-time.

916
01:29:34,787 --> 01:29:36,455
Ha-ha-ha.

917
01:29:36,497 --> 01:29:38,499
[chuckles]

918
01:29:41,710 --> 01:29:45,297
I got an idea how you
can talk to your wife.

919
01:29:45,339 --> 01:29:48,425
Wait till she's asleep.

920
01:29:48,467 --> 01:29:52,179
Then she'll listen to you
and she won't even know it.

921
01:29:59,311 --> 01:30:01,647
I'm not gonna see you anymore, am I?

922
01:30:04,483 --> 01:30:07,736
I think we said
everything we needed to say.

923
01:30:07,820 --> 01:30:11,824
Maybe it's time to say things
to someone closer to you.

924
01:30:13,700 --> 01:30:17,496
Maybe we can pretend like we're
gonna see each other tomorrow.

925
01:30:19,373 --> 01:30:21,375
Just for pretend.

926
01:30:27,798 --> 01:30:29,633
OK.

927
01:30:34,346 --> 01:30:36,348
I'm gonna go now.

928
01:30:43,105 --> 01:30:45,816
I'll see you tomorrow, Cole.

929
01:31:06,044 --> 01:31:08,213
[siren wailing]

930
01:31:09,798 --> 01:31:12,634
[chatter on police radio]

931
01:31:12,718 --> 01:31:16,013
L-I'm OK, officer. I-I'm OK.

932
01:31:16,054 --> 01:31:18,223
I don't know what happened.

933
01:31:24,062 --> 01:31:25,898
[Lynn] Hmm.

934
01:31:26,899 --> 01:31:29,735
Jeez, I hope nobody got hurt.

935
01:31:33,363 --> 01:31:36,116
You're very quiet.

936
01:31:36,200 --> 01:31:39,536
You're mad I missed
the play, aren't you?

937
01:31:39,578 --> 01:31:42,247
I have two jobs, baby.

938
01:31:42,331 --> 01:31:45,459
You know how important
they are for us.

939
01:31:45,542 --> 01:31:47,294
[sighs]

940
01:31:47,377 --> 01:31:50,047
I'd give anything to have been there.

941
01:32:01,934 --> 01:32:04,603
I'm ready to communicate with you now.

942
01:32:09,358 --> 01:32:11,193
Communicate?

943
01:32:12,986 --> 01:32:15,322
Tell you my secrets.

944
01:32:17,074 --> 01:32:19,076
What is it?

945
01:32:23,288 --> 01:32:25,958
You know the accident up there?

946
01:32:26,041 --> 01:32:27,876
Yeah?

947
01:32:29,169 --> 01:32:31,296
Someone got hurt.

948
01:32:31,338 --> 01:32:33,465
They did?

949
01:32:33,549 --> 01:32:35,384
A lady.

950
01:32:37,177 --> 01:32:39,471
She died.

951
01:32:39,555 --> 01:32:42,057
Oh, my God. What, you can see her?

952
01:32:43,267 --> 01:32:45,102
Yes.

953
01:32:45,143 --> 01:32:47,145
Where is she?

954
01:32:50,023 --> 01:32:52,526
Standing next to my window.

955
01:32:59,825 --> 01:33:01,827
Cole, you're scaring me.

956
01:33:03,203 --> 01:33:05,664
They scare me too sometimes.

957
01:33:07,708 --> 01:33:09,543
They?

958
01:33:13,463 --> 01:33:15,340
Ghosts.

959
01:33:18,885 --> 01:33:21,221
You see ghosts, Cole?

960
01:33:24,182 --> 01:33:27,227
They want me to do things for them.

961
01:33:29,730 --> 01:33:32,190
They... they talk to you?

962
01:33:32,232 --> 01:33:35,360
They tell you to do things?

963
01:33:35,402 --> 01:33:38,572
They're the ones that used to hurt me.

964
01:33:40,699 --> 01:33:43,660
What are you thinking, Mama?

965
01:33:43,702 --> 01:33:45,871
You think I'm a freak?

966
01:33:45,912 --> 01:33:48,165
Look at my face.

967
01:33:48,206 --> 01:33:51,418
I would never think
that about you. Ever.

968
01:33:52,586 --> 01:33:55,088
- Got it?
- Got it.

969
01:34:02,220 --> 01:34:04,556
Just let me think for a minute.

970
01:34:08,310 --> 01:34:10,562
Grandma says hi.

971
01:34:13,857 --> 01:34:17,069
She says she's sorry for
taking the bumblebee pendant.

972
01:34:17,110 --> 01:34:19,279
She just likes it a lot.

973
01:34:21,657 --> 01:34:23,492
What?

974
01:34:23,575 --> 01:34:26,244
Grandma comes to visit me sometimes.

975
01:34:28,413 --> 01:34:30,957
Cole, that's very wrong.

976
01:34:31,041 --> 01:34:34,044
- Grandma's gone, you know that.
- I know.

977
01:34:34,086 --> 01:34:36,588
- She wanted me to tell you...
- Cole, please stop.

978
01:34:36,630 --> 01:34:39,299
She wanted me to tell you
she saw you dance.

979
01:34:41,718 --> 01:34:45,305
She said... when you were little,

980
01:34:45,389 --> 01:34:47,557
you and her had a fight

981
01:34:47,599 --> 01:34:50,435
right before your dance recital.

982
01:34:54,106 --> 01:34:57,609
You thought she didn't
come to see you dance.

983
01:35:01,196 --> 01:35:03,365
She did.

984
01:35:08,745 --> 01:35:11,581
She hid in the back
so you wouldn't see.

985
01:35:12,666 --> 01:35:15,627
She said you were like an angel.

986
01:35:20,215 --> 01:35:22,384
She said...

987
01:35:22,467 --> 01:35:25,637
...you came to the place
where they buried her...

988
01:35:27,973 --> 01:35:30,308
...asked her a question.

989
01:35:32,936 --> 01:35:35,605
She said the answer is...

990
01:35:37,399 --> 01:35:39,526
..."Every day"-

991
01:35:41,945 --> 01:35:44,281
What did you ask?

992
01:35:52,497 --> 01:35:54,166
Do...

993
01:35:55,709 --> 01:35:58,545
Do I make her proud?

994
01:36:02,007 --> 01:36:04,551
Mama.

995
01:36:22,736 --> 01:36:25,238
[people laughing on TV]

996
01:36:33,330 --> 01:36:35,248
<i>[man] Hi, everybody.</i>

997
01:36:35,332 --> 01:36:38,919
<i>As most of you know,
I'm not used to doing this,</i>

998
01:36:39,002 --> 01:36:42,881
<i>and, uh, I promised Anna that
I'd try not to embarrass her.</i>

999
01:36:42,964 --> 01:36:44,966
<i>I'll leave that to her mother.</i>

1000
01:36:45,050 --> 01:36:46,802
[chuckling]

1001
01:36:46,885 --> 01:36:49,262
<i>But we do want to thank
all of you for coming</i>

1002
01:36:49,346 --> 01:36:52,098
<i>and for sharing this
wonderful day with us.</i>

1003
01:36:52,182 --> 01:36:54,601
<i>It's, uh... bittersweet,
almost, for me,</i>

1004
01:36:54,684 --> 01:36:57,312
<i>because I hate giving her up...</i>

1005
01:36:57,395 --> 01:36:59,397
Anna?

1006
01:37:09,533 --> 01:37:11,535
<i>I miss you.</i>

1007
01:37:17,123 --> 01:37:20,001
I miss you too.

1008
01:37:20,085 --> 01:37:22,921
Why, Malcolm?

1009
01:37:23,839 --> 01:37:25,674
What?

1010
01:37:27,425 --> 01:37:31,096
- What is it? What?
- Why did you leave me?

1011
01:37:31,179 --> 01:37:34,015
I didn't leave you.

1012
01:37:37,602 --> 01:37:39,938
[clattering]

1013
01:37:54,953 --> 01:37:57,122
[Cole] <i>I</i> see people.

1014
01:37:58,957 --> 01:38:01,501
They don't know they're dead.

1015
01:38:04,671 --> 01:38:07,841
<i>[Malcolm] How often do you see them?</i>

1016
01:38:07,924 --> 01:38:10,427
<i>All the time.</i>

1017
01:38:13,054 --> 01:38:14,973
<i>They're everywhere.</i>

1018
01:38:25,317 --> 01:38:28,862
<i>They only see what they want to see.</i>

1019
01:38:33,199 --> 01:38:35,994
[Malcolm] OK, Mikey.

1020
01:38:37,829 --> 01:38:41,166
<i>Come on. Give me a minute.</i>

1021
01:39:11,738 --> 01:39:14,032
- [gunshot]
- [groaning]

1022
01:39:14,074 --> 01:39:16,201
[Anna screams]

1023
01:39:16,242 --> 01:39:18,912
[sobbing]

1024
01:39:18,995 --> 01:39:21,498
- Oh, God. Oh, God, honey.
- [groaning]

1025
01:39:21,539 --> 01:39:23,541
- Did Vincent...
- Let me see.

1026
01:39:23,583 --> 01:39:25,251
It doesn't even hurt.

